{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, dynamic segmentation can be leveraged to detect significant changes in sensor data distribution that are likely associated with changes in the performed activities [3].",
    "We believe that dynamic segmentation would allow LLMs to process more meaningful information to reliably perform ADL recognition.",
    "Open-world HARFor the sake of this work, we constrained the LLM in predicting the most likely activity among a set of candidates.",
    "This is the most common approach in the ADLs recognition literature.",
    "However, this is a limitation, since in real-life deployments we can not foresee in advance all the possible activities carried out by the subject."
  ]
}